   <body>
      <prereq>
         <indexterm>controller box</indexterm>
         <indexterm>Tuner</indexterm>
         <note>The update of the firmware on the controller box can be done
via a RS232 serial connection.</note>
      </prereq>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Connect your laptop to the service port (J223) located
on the front side of the controller box.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/main_controller_service_port_0000116520.svg"
                         scope="local"
                         translate="no"
                         xml:lang="en"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
               <note>Use the service port cable 940â€“0024D for the proper
connection of all required signals.</note>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Launch the UPS Tuner and select <uicontrol>Controller Box</uicontrol>. After start-up, your laptop will automatically log in and the main
menu appears on the terminal screen.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <note>Navigate through the menu tree by typing the number
of the submenu you wish to enter.</note>
            </stepxmp>
            <stepxmp>
               <table>
                  <tgroup cols="1">
                     <colspec colname="col1"/>
                     <tbody>
                        <row>
                           <entry>
                              <screen xml:space="preserve">&gt;&gt; Welcome to Service Port Main Menu &lt;&lt;1: Configure Factory Settings (Locked)2: Configure System Parameters3: System Information Inquiry4: Upgrade Controller Firmware5: System Reboot/Shutdown0: End Session   Choose [1-5, 0]:</screen>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Type 4 (<uicontrol translate="no">Upgrade Controller Firmware</uicontrol>).</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Select the <uicontrol>Send file</uicontrol> function for
the terminal application to transfer the new firmware hex file to
the SRAM.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Type 1 (<uicontrol>Erase FLASH &amp; program new code</uicontrol>) to program the code into the flash memory.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <table>
                  <tgroup cols="1">
                     <colspec colname="col1"/>
                     <tbody>
                        <row>
                           <entry>
                              <screen xml:space="preserve">Download complete - HEX data is validSelection:1. Erase FLASH  &amp; program new code9. Abort &amp; Exit   Choose [1, 9]:</screen>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Type <uicontrol>y</uicontrol> to confirm the update and
copy the new firmware from the SRAM to the FLASH memory.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <note>If you wish to cancel the update and keep the old firmware,
press the <uicontrol>ESC</uicontrol> key.</note>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Restart the system.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
